<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,402,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
This is a Madagascan endemic genus of about 15 described species, including the synonymised genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lees et al. 2003)" baseAuthorityName="Lees" baseAuthorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Miraja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1368,403,426]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Miraja</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lees, D. C. &amp; Kremen, C. &amp; Raharitsimba, T." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="762 - 793" refId="ref35942" refString="Lees, D. C., Kremen, C. &amp; Raharitsimba, T. (2003) Classification, diversity, and endemism of the butterflies (Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea): a revised species checklist. In: Goodman, S. M. &amp; Benstead, J. P. (Eds.), The Natural History of Madagascar. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, pp. 762 - 793." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Lees 
<emphasis box="[151,199,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; considering material collected to date, the radiation is probably at least twice this size (D.C. Lees, pers. comm. 2013). In a future paper, we will report that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Oberthur)" baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" box="[741,1006,474,499]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Perrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiplaga">
<emphasis box="[741,879,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. albiplaga</emphasis>
(Oberthür)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Oberthur)" baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" box="[1064,1294,474,499]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Perrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ismael">
<emphasis box="[1064,1165,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. ismael</emphasis>
(Oberthür)
</taxonomicName>
are bamboo feeders. Here we present limited information on a species reared from palm.
</paragraph>
